sep=: Story Title
I would like the React components to be refactored to be more modular.
We would like consistently formatted code with good documentation.
As a visitor to the site, I want the music data to be reliable (free of duplicates, accurate playlist track counts, etc)
As a mobile user, I want the text and card layouts to look refined.
As a developer, I would like to transfer our UML diagram to GitBook so it isn't tied to a specific utbox account.
As a visitor to the site, I want to see the title of the site on the tab in my browser.
We want our visualization to be available on our site at the path /visualization
As a developer, I would like to transfer our API documentation to GitBook so it can be collaboratively worked on in real time.
We want a presentation we can display in class hosted on GitPitch.
As a developer, I want to know our code works by using tests through selenium
As a visitor to the website, I would like to see a more useable and intuitive layout for detail pages.
As a visitor to the site, I would like to be able to sort my filtered results.
As a mobile visitor, I would like the results to fit on my device without needing to scroll.
As a developer, I would like a create a robust script that scrapes Spotify to augment our existing data.
As a visitor to the site, I would like to see a responsive About page that does not require me to click through various tabs.
As a visitor to the site, I would like to move through many results rather than having thousands of results all presented on a single page.
As an API user, I want to get a list of all the tracks in a paginated response.
As someone who searches the site, I would like the keyword I searched for to be highlighted in the results.
As a visitor to the site, I would like to get search results of all matches for a given search.

As a visitor to the site, I would like to be able to enter some text in a box on a results page and reduce the number of results to those that match my text, e.g. entering 'Shak' should include Shakira results.
As a visitor to the site, I would like to be able to sort the results based on the main "title" of the data, such as the song name on the songs page.
As a developer, I want to have a reproducible build environment that everyone on the team uses.
As a visitor to the site, I should be able to use the navbar or sidebar to navigate to other pages from within any specific page.
As a back-end developer, I would like for a push to the GitHub repo to trigger an automatic deployment of the site in production.
As a consumer of the API, I should be able to understand how to access and consume the API.
As a back-end developer, I want to be able to push my changes and have automatic feedback that my code passes tests.
As a front-end developer, I want to be able to push the site and see my changes in under 1 minute.
As an API developer, the models should be designed such that I am able to create an API around them
As a visitor to the site, I would like to search through all songs, artists, albums, and playlists.
As a visitor to the site, I should be able to see at least 3 playlists and 5 of their attributes in a grid on a "Playlists" page.
As a visitor to the site, I should be able to see at least 3 albums and 5 of their attributes in a grid on a "Albums" page.
As a visitor to the site, I should be able to see at least 3 artists and 5 of their attributes in a grid on a "Artists" page.
As a visitor to the site, I should be able to see at least 3 tracks and 5 of their attributes in a grid on a "Tracks" page.
As a consumer of the API, I should be able to query available artists
As a vistor to the site I should be able to visit an "About" page to see more information about the authors, technology, and purpose of the site.
As a consumer of the API, I would like to get a list of the albums for a specific artist.
As an initial visitor to the site, I would like a splash page of the data on the site to understand the purpose of the website.
As a visitor to the site, I should be able to navigate the site through a navbar or sidebar on mobile
As a frontend developer, I should be able to see a static hello world homepage to ensure that the backend and frontend stacks are working on a basic level.
As backend developer, A database should be set up such that I can store data in it
As a consumer of the API, I want to get a list of songs authored by any artist
